The paper deals with the decoding framework for Massive MIMO systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The proposed algorithm also involves parallel computing and load balancing, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the trade-offs between performance and complexity, which is a topic related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
